# Copy Review and Editing

## Dashes

Do not use em dashes (—) or en dashes (–). Use hyphens (-), commas, or rewrite the sentence instead.

- Bad: "The program — which launched last year — exceeded targets."
- Good: "The program, which launched last year, exceeded targets."

## UNOPS Usage

Never use the possessive form of UNOPS. Do not add an apostrophe or apostrophe-s after UNOPS. Rewrite to avoid the possessive.

- Bad: "UNOPS' mandate", "UNOPS's mission"
- Good: "the UNOPS mandate", "the mission of UNOPS"
